  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who embezzled a moderate sum of money ($25,000) and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. The spectator's outburst is legally irrelevant to the sentencing. Given the defendant's lack of prior criminal history and the non-violent nature of the white-collar crime, a lengthy prison sentence is unwarranted. A shorter period of incarceration is appropriate to provide deterrence and punishment, while also allowing the defendant to eventually continue paying back the embezzled funds.",
